parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially during heavy rain or snow.
symptoms: Windshield wipers stop working or work intermittently
and may not turn on at all; wipers may work only at high speed or not at all; wipers may stop in the middle of a cycle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front seat recliner handle can cause the seat to become unstable, leading to discomfort, distraction, and potentially, accidents.
A power seat short circuit can cause a fire, leading to property damage, injury, or even fatalities.
symptoms: the seat adjustment lever broke off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: or shifts erratically; vehicle will not move or accelerate; transmission fluid leaks; temperature display changes to Celsius when raining.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Axle and differential failure can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents.
symptoms: Axle breaks; rear differential leaks; rear axle noise; binding in front end.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Seat and mirror issues can cause discomfort and distraction while driving.
symptoms: Seat recliner lever breaks; driver's seat mirror vibrates; passenger seat mirror breaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Four-wheel drive issues can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle shifts into four-wheel drive without driver input; vehicle jumps into four-wheel drive intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical and fire hazards can cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Alternator light is on; temperature display changes to Celsius when raining; engine catches fire due to transmission fluid leak.
